excerpt: Massive mountainside sculpture drawing crowds for its depiction of 4 former American presidents.
detail_description: Mount Rushmore National Memorial is a massive mountainside sculpture featuring the depictions of four former American presidents. The idea for this monument was conceived by South Dakota State Historian Doane Robinson as a way to attract tourists and boost the economy of South Dakota. Sculptor Gutzon Borglum was hired to carve the granite spires, but he chose Mount Rushmore instead due to the fragility of the original site.
name: Mount Rushmore National Memorial

excerpt: Museum featuring life-sized wax replicas of U.S. presidents placed in historic scenes.
detail_description: The National Presidential Wax Museum, situated near Mount Rushmore in Keystone, South Dakota, is a must-visit attraction for history enthusiasts. Created by renowned wax artist Katherine Stubergh, the museum showcases over 100 lifelike wax sculptures of iconic American figures. Visitors can witness pivotal moments in U.S. presidential history through these meticulously crafted replicas. It's an educational and patriotic experience suitable for the entire family.
name: The National Presidential Wax Museum

excerpt: Mining museum in a replica 1895 gold mill, guided tours of an old goldmine, plus gold & gem panning.
detail_description: Located in Keystone, South Dakota, Big Thunder Gold Mine is a fascinating attraction that offers guided tours of an original gold mine from 1895. Visitors can immerse themselves in the history of the area and enjoy gold and gem panning activities. The site also features a National Presidential Wax Museum with over 100 lifelike wax sculptures of famous personalities, including all presidents. Additionally, visitors can camp near the Mount Rushmore National Memorial at Horse Thief Lake.
name: Big Thunder Gold Mine

detail_description: Dahl's Chainsaw Art, located in Keystone, is a must-visit for art enthusiasts and curious travelers. Founded by the talented Dahl brothers, Jarrett and Jordan, the gallery showcases their exceptional chainsaw carvings made from local woods like Black Hills Pine. With 15 years of experience, they have gained global recognition and won numerous awards for their unique pieces.
name: Dahl's Chainsaw Art
address: 121 Roy Street Highway 16A, Keystone, SD 57751, USA

detail_description: Nestled in the picturesque Black Hills Region, Holy Terror Mini Golf offers a fun and challenging 18-hole course named after Keystone's last active gold mine. The course features diverse terrain with steep hills, boulders, water wheels, and streams. Families can enjoy old-fashioned fun while putting around the scenic pine-laden slope.
name: Holy Terror Mini Golf

excerpt: Adventure park with chairlift, zip-line & treetop obstacle course, plus hiking & Mt. Rushmore views.
detail_description: Rushmore Tramway Adventures is an exciting adventure park offering a variety of family-friendly activities such as chairlift rides, zip-lines, treetop obstacle courses, and hiking with stunning views of Mount Rushmore. Visitors can also enjoy an alpine slide, tubing hill, jump tower, and an aerial adventure park suitable for all skill levels. The park provides adrenaline-pumping activities amidst the beautiful natural landscapes of Mt.
name: Rushmore Tramway Adventures

excerpt: Homey 1899 schoolhouse-turned-museum with early-life exhibits & Carrie Ingalls memorabilia.
detail_description: Nestled in a charming 1899 schoolhouse, the Keystone Historical Museum offers visitors a delightful glimpse into the rich cultural and historical tapestry of Keystone. This Victorian-style building served as an educational institution until 1988 and has since been transformed into a captivating museum. Inside, you'll discover fascinating exhibits featuring rock and mineral collections, art displays, and memorabilia dedicated to Carrie Ingalls from the beloved Little House series.
name: Keystone Museum

excerpt: History museum with paintings & carvings by the sculptor of Mount Rushmore, with a gift shop.
detail_description: The Borglum Story is a captivating museum located in Keystone, dedicated to the life and artistry of Gutzon Borglum, the visionary sculptor behind Mount Rushmore. As you step inside, you'll be greeted by an array of paintings and carvings that showcase his remarkable talent. The museum offers an insightful audio guide that enriches your experience as you delve into Borglum's personal journey and professional milestones.
name: Borglum Story

detail_description: Aerial Adventure Park is an amusement park with a variety of obstacle courses, suspension bridges, and zip lines. It is located in Keystone, SD and is popular with families.
name: Aerial Adventure Park @ RTA

excerpt: Family-friendly outfit for scenic railway tours through the Black Hills in historic steam trains.
detail_description: Step back in time and experience the charm of the 1880 Train - Keystone Depot, a family-friendly attraction offering scenic railway tours through the picturesque Black Hills on historic steam trains. The three-hour round-trip ride from Keystone to Hill City and back provides breathtaking views of the natural habitat and wildlife in the area. While onboard, you can indulge in snacks like nachos, pretzels, pizza, and sweet treats at their High-Liner Snack Shoppe.
name: 1880 Train - Keystone Depot

excerpt: Classic coffee beverages alongside a wine & provisions shop with lounge seating, patio, & games.
detail_description: Grapes & Grinds is a charming establishment that offers a unique combination of freshly roasted coffee and fine wines, making it an ideal destination for both locals and travelers. Situated in the heart of Keystone, not far from Mt Rushmore, it provides a perfect setting to relax and savor the beauty of the Black Hills. The inviting atmosphere includes lounge seating, a patio with picturesque views, and even games for entertainment.
name: Grapes & Grinds

excerpt: Visitors race against their reflections in this indoor obstacle course with dead-ends & switchbacks.
detail_description: Keystone Fun Zone is a fun place for kids and adults alike. It has an arcade, a Mirror maze, and a brewery. The arcade is great for kids to play games and the Mirror maze is a fun way for them to see their reflections in every direction. The brewery is also really cool, as it's allowed visitors to drink beer inside. Overall, Keystone Fun Zone is a great place to visit if you're looking for some fun entertainment.
name: Keystone Fun Zone

detail_description: Mount Rushmore in Keystone, South Dakota offers a self-guided audio driving tour around the Black Hills. Despite some initial skepticism, visitors have been pleasantly surprised by the grandeur and detail of the monument. The site can get busy, especially during holidays, but it's worth exploring for its historical significance and picturesque surroundings.
name: Mt Rushmore

excerpt: Adventure park featuring Rushmore Cave, a roller coaster, a challenge course, a zipline & more.
name: Rush Mountain Adventure Park

detail_description: The Lincoln Borglum Visitor Center is a must-visit when heading to Mount Rushmore. Inside, you'll find an exhibit hall with extensive information about the creation of the granite sculptures and a 24-minute film detailing the carving process. While there, take a short walk on the Presidential Trail and explore the display museum. Although currently undergoing renovations until May 2019, this center offers an enriching experience for visitors eager to learn about the history and significance of Mount Rushmore.
name: Lincoln Borglum Visitor Center

excerpt: Casual motel with simple rooms, satellite TV & an outdoor heated pool, plus free WiFi & breakfast.
detail_description: Brookside Motel is a small, simple motel with basic rooms and an outdoor heated pool. It offers free WiFi and breakfast.
name: The Brookside Motel
